cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with identifying salient points in images, which is a crucial component of visual odometry, Structure-from-Motion or SLAM algorithms. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel keypoint-network architecture that is especially amenable to robust keypoint detection and description. 

The paper also involves self-supervised learning, which is a popular topic in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. 

The paper's focus on keypoint detection and matching could also place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. 

The paper's use of sub-pixel convolutions to upsample descriptor feature-maps could place it in the Robotics (cs.RO) category, as this technique is commonly used in robotics applications. 

Finally, the paper's use of neural networks and deep learning techniques could place it in the Neural Networks (cs.NE) category.
